 from speedy engr latech edu speedy mercer subject re living organization louisiana tech university lines two five nntp posting host bhm one one six e spc engr latech edu in article pooder rchland vnet ibm com don fearn writes in article c seven zero a zero zero zero writes i sprained my right ankle once and kept riding when i broke my right leg in two places i had knee surgery while i was in the navy back in seven seven the doctors put me in a cast from ass to ankle my only method of transportaion was a dohc four five zero honda at the time i found that by sliding back on the seat i could use my heel did i mention it was my left leg to operate the shift i would hook the end of the lever with my heel and lift my entire leg for up shifts and just drop my leg on the lever for the down shifts forget nutral took way too much finesse for the leg the crutches were bungee corded to the right side of the bike with the top resting on the passenger peg and the right turnsignal sticking through the hole in the crutches every other day when i rode the one zero miles to physical therapy tourture sessions the doc would give me hell about riding a bike much less riding in my condition didn t stop me tho b p btw this is the same bike i assembled in my second floor barracks room and rode down the stairs when it was completed i am not paid to have an opinion dr speed suzuki gs eight five zero g dod eight one seven seven